Go to EC2 Console
Launch EC2 Console (choose ubantu, open port 5000, 80, 143, 22).
connect via ssh.
install pip : apt-get -y install pip
install python: apt-get -y install python
install virtualenv: pip install virtualenv
install awsebcli: pip install virtualenv
Create Virtual Env:
      1. virtualenv ~/eb-virt
      2. source ~/eb-virt/bin/activate
      3. pip install flask
      4. pip install flask_pymongo
      5. pip install PyMongo
      6. pip install flask_restful
      7. pip install flask_cors
      8. pip freeze 
Create a Flask Application:
      1.source ~/eb-virt/bin/activate
      2.mkdir eb-flask
      3.cd eb-flask
      4.sudo nano application.yml
      5.paste your code
      6.relplace app.run with "app.run(host='0.0.0.0',debug=True)"
      7.ctrl+x Y Enter
Run: python application.py
Ctrl + C to stop.
Screen python application.py - use to keep running server after close terminal.
To stop : screen -l & screen -r "sessionid".

      

